        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer32542203" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8093706285614768968">Every page of this book is packed with gorgeous, poetic writing and jaw-dropping, often hilarious psychological observation. Proust does not prop himself up with over-complex structures, is not confusing, is not gratuitously strange. He understood life preternaturally well and wrote about it preternaturally well. This is the novel of all novels. But read cautiously: Proust <i>will</i> dissect your most intimate thoughts and motivations, and he will be as accurate as a sniper. <br/><br/>&quot;All our final decisions a</span>
  <span id="freeText8093706285614768968" style="display:none">Every page of this book is packed with gorgeous, poetic writing and jaw-dropping, often hilarious psychological observation. Proust does not prop himself up with over-complex structures, is not confusing, is not gratuitously strange. He understood life preternaturally well and wrote about it preternaturally well. This is the novel of all novels. But read cautiously: Proust <i>will</i> dissect your most intimate thoughts and motivations, and he will be as accurate as a sniper. <br /><br />"All our final decisions are made in a state of mind that is not going to last."</span>
